President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to appoint Roger D. Carstens as the Special Presidential Envoy for Hostage Affairs. Carstens is currently a Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Bureau of Democracy, Human Rights, and Labor at the Department of State. He has previously worked with international NGOs in Somalia and Jordan, providing humanitarian assistance and stability support to Syrian refugees and internally displaced persons. Carstens also served in the United States Army for 20 years, including in the Special Forces and 1st Ranger Battalion. He holds a master's degree from the United States Naval War College and St. John's College.